                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> 9. I never had to do any qvox/hs jumping in the deep, just didn't go near the see-invis mobs. Then crossed the invisible bridge and took the first left in the thought horror tunnels then set up cmap before the tunnel curves right. Think I was there for about 2 hours and had 3 drop in that time. I was also using pet feign to split them up, tried a few times  with darkness/fd but it only worked once and was a pain.<br /><br />3. I also charmed the sun revenants in the grey, WoT hardly ever breaks and with a hasted pet you spend most of the time waiting for re-pops. I got my shard on the 4th kill and since then have helped a few friends get thiers, took 3-4 clearings of the camp for those ones to drop.<br /><br />7. With the fungus grove shard once you've cleared the priest and 2 warriors at the back of the room (they're at the back if your facing the direction you entered from) you have plenty of room to kite them round. Took me 5 hours of killing to get my shard <img src="images/hypnotized_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /> but some friends got theirs a lot faster than that.<br /><br />5. I went to sanctus seru  instead of katta for that shard and it sucked please don't spend 6 hours killing those stupid mobs and try katta first.<img src="images/azumaan.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br />Getting the sceptre was the hardest part I did solo, once you find the place just run to the altar and hope you channel fd. Pre-nerf CoS was extremely helpful here. If you look at the map in the first post the place your looking for is just to the right of the 'Perhaps Va`Dyn with PH spawns here', text. probably really close to where the 500 line crosses the -500 vertical line.<br /><br />I ended up grouping for the ssra shard and nothing new to add for any of the other ones.</span id="msg"></font><br><br>